WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.100
these are my disclosures so i think everyone here is aware that the presence of sinus involvement

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:13.260
and aggressive B-cell non-hydrogel lymphoma is associated with poor outcomes and even patients

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:17.620
who are able to proceed with CAR-T or autologous stem cell transplant and these are the best

00:00:17.620 --> 00:00:22.420
treatments we have for patients with relapsed sinus involvement and these patients still have

00:00:22.420 --> 00:00:27.700
poor outcomes and unfortunately most of them progress a relapse so there's definitely a high

00:00:27.700 --> 00:00:35.600
unmet clinical need for these patients. We also know that the CD20-Bispecific have a

00:00:35.600 --> 00:00:41.380
favorable safety profile and high efficacy in patients with systemic relapsed or refractory

00:00:41.380 --> 00:00:46.640
aggressive B-cell non-hydrogel lymphoma including DLBCL, high-grade B-cell lymphoma and mantle cell

00:00:46.640 --> 00:00:52.140
lymphoma. But we have limited data on their activity and safety in patients with sinus

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:57.220
involvement as these patients were excluded from the pivotal clinical trials. However,

00:00:57.400 --> 00:01:02.580
we we have emerging data that show that these antibodies are actually active in sinus involvement.

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:08.940
So I've listed here a few small series. There's a series from Dave and colleagues from UPenn that had

00:01:08.940 --> 00:01:17.500
seven patients treated with Glofit, three patients achieved CR and 2PR. Dr. Brooks here and his large

00:01:17.500 --> 00:01:22.180
multi-center retrospective study had five responsive valuable patients with sinus involvement.

00:01:22.180 --> 00:01:27.100
Unfortunately, none of them responded and there's a small case series of three patients with Burkitt lymphoma

00:01:27.100 --> 00:01:33.100
treated with Glofit and Paula, one of whom had leptomeningeal disease and achieved CR.

00:01:35.980 --> 00:01:40.620
There are two important studies that show that the Bispecific can actually cross the

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:46.380
blood-brain barrier and in these two studies that it was was Glofitamab. Gottfried from the

00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:52.300
City of Hope had four patients and there's another series from Europe with eight patients and in both

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:56.800
of these series patients received a patient with sinus involvement received Glofitamab.

00:01:56.800 --> 00:02:05.680
And Glofitamab was detected in the CSF at very small concentrations only 0.1 to 0.4% of plasma concentrations.

00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:13.360
But patient-derived CSF samples were able to induce T-cell cytotoxicity against B-cells

00:02:13.920 --> 00:02:19.040
and in both series response clinical responses were seen without neurotoxicity.

