00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:29.200
as a part of multi-center retrospective study of patients with different types of aggressive

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:35.660
B-Cell Null Hodgkin lymphoma treated at six U.S. medical centers, part of the Cuban Consortium.

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:42.920
This work was led by Kiran Turan, who's a fellow at MD Anderson. We had two cohorts,

00:02:42.920 --> 00:02:47.640
one cohort with active CNS involvement and had 18 patients. So these are patients who had active

00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:52.080
CNS disease at the time of the bispecific treatment initiation. But we also had a cohort

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:57.120
of patients with history of CNS involvement, but not active CNS disease at the time of the

00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:01.900
bispecific treatment initiation, because in many of the pivotal trials, patients with history of

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:09.300
CNS involvement, even if not active, at enrollment were excluded. These are the baseline characteristics

00:03:09.300 --> 00:03:14.680
for the two cohorts. Most patients received Glofit, but a small number of patients received

00:03:14.680 --> 00:03:19.940
Epcor or Mocin. Most patients had DL-BCL and high-grade B-Cell lymphoma, but we had two

00:03:19.940 --> 00:03:22.060
patients with Burkitt, mantle cell lymphoma, and primate.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:35.840
In the active CNS cohort, 12 out of the 18 patients received the bispecific in combination

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:42.420
with other active agents, including BTKI, chemo, radiation, polatuzumab, or lenalidomide.

00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:49.580
I'm going to focus on the outcomes for the active CNS cohort. So the median duration of the

00:03:49.580 --> 00:03:54.460
Bispecific therapy was only two and a half months. So it's a very short follow-up

00:03:54.460 --> 00:04:02.360
duration. The overall response rate was 56%, including CR and 33%. The CNS overall response

00:04:02.360 --> 00:04:09.740
rate was 65%, including CR in six patients or 35%. And the median time to response was

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:16.260
short, 1.8 months. In the six months, PFS rate was 43%, and the six-month CNS PFS rate

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:19.560
was 53%. And the six-month overall survival rate was 53%. So the median response rate was

00:04:19.580 --> 00:04:23.420
77%.

00:04:23.420 --> 00:04:28.000
We tried to look at outcomes in different subgroups, but the numbers are very small,

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.880
so this is all just hypothesis generating. If you look at the last column to the right,

00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:40.120
the CNS CR rate, we saw CRs with Glofit and also EPCo in patients with parenchymal disease

00:04:40.120 --> 00:04:46.080
or leptomeningeal disease when the bispecific was given as monotherapy or in combination.

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:48.120
We saw CRs in DLBCL and primate.

00:04:48.120 --> 00:04:49.080
So this is all just hypothesis generating. If you look at the last column to the right,

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:49.080
the CNS CR rate, we saw CRs with Glofit and also EPCo in patients with parenchymal disease or leptomeningeal disease when the bispecific was given as monotherapy or in combination. We saw CRs in DLBCL and primate.

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:53.800
primary CNS lymphoma, but not in high-grade or mantle cell lymphoma, but again, very small

00:04:53.800 --> 00:05:00.000
numbers. Importantly, the CR rates seem to be similar in patients with prior CAR-T or CAR-T

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:08.120
naive patients. And then these are the survival curves. We looked at the outcomes with monotherapy

00:05:08.120 --> 00:05:15.520
versus combination, and we didn't see differences. Importantly, with a median follow-up of 12 months,

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:21.340
we had six patients who achieved CNS-CR, who also had systemic CR, and none of these six

00:05:21.340 --> 00:05:26.040
patients relapsed or received subsequent treatment with CAR-T or ALO or anything else,

00:05:26.380 --> 00:05:34.700
which suggests that these CRs could be lasting. And then in terms of toxicity, we looked at CRS

00:05:34.700 --> 00:05:41.420
and ICANS. The CRS rate in the overall cohort was 43%, which is what you'd expect, but the ICANS

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:45.480
rate was a little bit higher than expected, 25% of seven patients.

00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:51.760
And the ICANS rate was high in both the prior and the active CNS cohort, so 30%, or three out of 10

00:05:51.760 --> 00:05:57.460
patients in patients with prior history of CNS involvement, and 22% in patients with active

00:05:57.460 --> 00:06:04.360
CNS involvement, which included grades two, three, and four. We looked at these seven patients with

00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:11.960
ICANS, four had DL-BCL, two had mantle cell lymphoma, one had high-grade BCL, six patients

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:15.460
received Glowfit, and one Epco. Five of them received Glowfit, and one received Glowfit.

00:06:15.460 --> 00:06:15.500
So we looked at these seven patients with ICANS, four had DL-BCL, two had mantle cell lymphoma,

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:20.900
received it in combination, four didn't develop CRS, and none of the four patients with active

00:06:20.900 --> 00:06:25.620
CNS lymphoma who developed ICANS achieved CR, but three did respond and achieved PR.

00:06:26.920 --> 00:06:32.060
There was another important study presented at ASH last year. I don't have their slides,

00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:36.940
so I just included data from the abstract. It was a multi-center retrospective study

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:42.840
from Europe of patients with CNS involvement by B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma treated by Specifex.

00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:45.440
The median final lines of

00:06:45.440 --> 00:06:50.200
treatment were three, and almost half of the patients received prior CAR-T. In this series,

00:06:50.300 --> 00:06:56.440
most patients received Epco, 73%. The overall response rate and CR rates were very similar to

00:06:56.440 --> 00:07:03.100
our study, 66% and 37%, but the CR rate seemed to be higher with the combination. The median PFS

00:07:03.100 --> 00:07:09.060
was 8.5 months, and the ICANS rate also in the study was higher than in patients without,

00:07:09.780 --> 00:07:13.520
